24/04/2005
VILNIUS, Lithuania -- Turkish Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul said Friday (22 April) that his country was on track with the democratic reforms required for EU membership. He denied reports of a slowdown, saying that EU accession continues to be the cabinet's top priority and that its resolve has remained unchanged. The Turkey-EU Association Council is due to meet in Luxembourg on Tuesday to discuss preparations for the launch of accession talks in the autumn. Gul was in Vilnius for an informal meeting of NATO foreign ministers. (AFP - 22/04/05) 
